==On Earth==

* '''[[1912]]''' - Author [[Barbara Strachey]] is born.
* '''[[1918]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] attends a medical board examination in Kingston-upon-Hull.
* '''[[1971]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter 325]].
* '''[[1981]]''' - ''[[The Tolkien Quiz Book (by Robinson and Wilson)|The Tolkien Quiz Book]]'', the book by Robinson and Wilson, is published.
* '''[[1982]]''' - The first episode of the new version of the [[The Lord of the Rings (1981 radio series)|1981 radio series]] of ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]'' is aired on [[BBC|BBC Radio 4]].
* '''[[1985]]''' - [[Robert Havard]], [[Inklings|Inkling]], dies.
* '''[[1998]]''' - Author [[Paul H. Kocher]] dies.
* '''[[1998]]''' - [[Mythcon 29]] in [[wikipedia:Wheaton, Illinois|Wheaton, Illinois]].
* '''[[2004]]''' - [[The Lord of the Rings Symphony]] in [[wikipedia:Seattle|Seattle]], [[wikipedia:Washington (state)|Washington]].
* '''[[2009]]''' - [[Mythcon 40]] in [[wikipedia:Los Angeles|Los Angeles]], [[wikipedia:California|California]].
* '''[[2010]]''' - [[Tolkien Thing]] 2010 in [[wikipedia:Bad Hersfeld|Bad Hersfeld]], [[wikipedia:Germany|Germany]].
* '''[[2010]]''' - [[Mythcon 41]] in [[wikipedia:Dallas|Dallas]], [[wikipedia:Texas|Texas]].
* '''[[2011]]''' - [[Tolkien Thing]] 2011 in [[wikipedia:Breuberg|Breuberg]], [[wikipedia:Germany|Germany]].
